50|$|The {{strategy}} holds long/short equity positions, with <b>long</b> <b>positions</b> hedged {{with short}} {{positions in the}} same and related sectors, so that the equity-market-neutral investor should be little affected by sector-wide events. This places, in essence, a bet that the <b>long</b> <b>positions</b> will outperform their sectors (or the short positions will under perform) regardless {{of the strength of}} the sectors. Equity-market-neutral strategy occupies a distinct place in the hedge fund landscape by exhibiting one of the lowest correlations with other alternative strategies.|$|E
