50|$|The term {{synthetic}} CDO arises {{because the}} cash {{flows from the}} premiums (via the component CDS in the portfolio) are analogous to the cash flows arising from mortgage or other obligations that are aggregated and paid to regular CDO buyers. In other words, taking the <b>long</b> <b>position</b> on a synthetic CDO (i.e., receiving regular premium payments) is like taking the <b>long</b> <b>position</b> on a normal CDO (i.e., receiving regular interest payments on mortgage bonds or credit card bonds contained within the CDO).|$|R
