5000|$|Open {{interest}} {{is the number of}} [...] "open" [...] contracts of derivatives like futures and options that have a time limit after which they expire. Open interest in a derivative is the sum of all contracts that have not expired, been exercised or physically delivered.Moreover, the open {{interest is}} the number of <b>long</b> <b>positions</b> or, equivalently, the number of short positions.|$|E
